REVENUE GENERATED VS REVENUE REALISED¶

In [622]:
bookings['is_cancelled'] = bookings['booking_status'] == 'Cancelled'
bookings['is_checked_out'] = bookings['booking_status'] == 'Checked Out'

# Grouping
revenue_summary = bookings.groupby('booking_status')[['revenue_generated', 'revenue_realized']].sum().reset_index()
revenue_summary['realized_pct'] = (revenue_summary['revenue_realized'] / revenue_summary['revenue_generated']) * 100

# Plot
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))

bar_width = 0.35
index = range(len(revenue_summary))

ax.bar(index, revenue_summary['revenue_generated'], bar_width, label='Revenue Generated', color='steelblue')
ax.bar([i + bar_width for i in index], revenue_summary['revenue_realized'], bar_width, label='Revenue Realized', color='seagreen')

ax.set_xlabel('Booking Status')
ax.set_ylabel('Revenue (in millions)')
ax.set_title('Revenue Generated vs Realized by Booking Status')
ax.set_xticks([i + bar_width / 2 for i in index])
ax.set_xticklabels(revenue_summary['booking_status'])
ax.legend()


ax.get_yaxis().set_major_formatter(plt.FuncFormatter(lambda x, loc: f'{int(x / 1e6)}M'))

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
